## What to do
Create Step 4 of the wizard — PDS upload with auth gate. Reference: C:\Users\infec\MyFolders\Documents\Work\Gainforest\green_globe\src\app\upload\_components\UploadStep.tsx

### Props
```ts
type UploadStepProps = {
  validRows: ValidatedRow[];
  onBack: () => void;
  onComplete: () => void;
};
```

### Auth pattern
The (upload) layout already enforces auth — session.isLoggedIn is checked in the layout. So the UploadStep can assume authentication. But for robustness, still implement sessionStorage preservation:
- Key: 'upload-trees-pending'
- Save: { validRows, timestamp } to sessionStorage before any OAuth redirect
- Restore: on mount, check sessionStorage; if data exists and < 10 min old, use it

### tRPC mutations
```ts
const createOccurrence = trpc.dwc.occurrence.create.useMutation();
const createMeasurement = trpc.dwc.measurement.create.useMutation();
```

### Upload flow (sequential per row):
```ts
for (const row of validRows) {
  setRowStatus(row.index, 'uploading');
  try {
    // 1. Create occurrence
    const occResult = await createOccurrence.mutateAsync({
      scientificName: row.occurrence.scientificName,
      eventDate: row.occurrence.eventDate,
      decimalLatitude: String(row.occurrence.decimalLatitude),
      decimalLongitude: String(row.occurrence.decimalLongitude),
      // ...other fields, only include if defined
    });
    // 2. Create measurement (if floraMeasurement is not null)
    if (row.floraMeasurement) {
      await createMeasurement.mutateAsync({
        occurrenceRef: occResult.uri,
        flora: {
          dbh: row.floraMeasurement.dbh,
          totalHeight: row.floraMeasurement.totalHeight,
          basalDiameter: row.floraMeasurement.diameter,
          canopyCoverPercent: row.floraMeasurement.canopyCoverPercent,
        },
      });
    }
    setRowStatus(row.index, 'success', occResult.uri);
  } catch (err) {
    setRowStatus(row.index, 'error', String(err));
  }
}
```

### Per-row status tracking:
```ts
type RowStatus =
  | { state: 'pending' }
  | { state: 'uploading' }
  | { state: 'success'; occurrenceUri: string }
  | { state: 'error'; error: string };
```

### UI:
- Progress bar with count (N/Total)
- List of rows with status icons (spinner/check/X)
- On completion: summary (N successes, N failures)
- 'Upload More Data' button (resets wizard) and 'Done' button

### Key: lat/lon must be converted to strings for the mutation input (ATProto stores them as strings)

## Don't
- Don't implement auth from scratch (layout handles it)
- Don't use raw fetch/agent (use tRPC mutations)
- Don't upload in parallel (sequential to avoid PDS rate limits)

